  "text": "Artificial lighting in show caves provides energy for the development of phototrophic lampenflora. Lampenflora are initially comprised of prokaryotic cyanobacteria and eukaryotic algae which form on surfaces of rock and speleothems adjacent to the lights [CITATION_1] . Lampenflora provide a nutrient base for microbes and primary consumer level arthropods.",
